modules.description: This module implements TLS-secured network communication using Miou's asynchronous I/O, providing client and server handshake initialization, data transmission, and session management. It operates on file descriptors through `Tls_miou_unix.t`, handling encrypted reads, writes, and connection lifecycle operations such as shutdown and close. Concrete use cases include establishing secure client connections to a remote TLS server and setting up TLS-secured listening sockets for incoming connections.
